A Saṅgha of a Thousand Nuns
At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Royal Monastery
Then a Saṅgha of a thousand nuns went up to the Buddha bowed and stood to one side
The Buddha said to them
Nuns a noble disciple who has four things is a streamenterer not liable to be reborn in the underworld bound for awakening
What four
Its when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha 
the teaching 
the Saṅgha 
And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones  leading to immersion
