Another Chapter of Abbreviated Texts on the Ganges Etc
Sloping East Etc
Mendicants the Ganges river slants slopes and inclines to the east
In the same way a mendicant who develops and cultivates the five powers slants slopes and inclines to extinguishment
And how does a mendicant who develops the five powers slant slope and incline to extinguishment
Its when a mendicant develops the powers of faith energy mindfulness immersion and wisdom which culminate in the removal of greed hate and delusion
Thats how a mendicant who develops and cultivates the five powers slants slopes and inclines to extinguishment
Six on slanting to the east
and six on slanting to the ocean
these two sixes make twelve
and thats how this chapter is recited
